0.text:
Hi we’re Cara Delevingne’s eyebrows. You
might recognise us from our latest ad campaigns

6.text:
for Coca Cola, as the Nike swoosh, or the
latest apple product the iBrows.

10.text:
Cara Delevingne: Hey, why do people only want
to talk to my eyebrows? There’s so much

15.text:
more to a model than just how she looks, you
have to be able to walk too... and turn! Hi

21.text:
I’m Cara Delevingne and I can’t wait to
walk you through my life, just remember it

25.text:
goes heel, toe, heel, toe. But like I said
there’s much more to it than that.

29.text:
I was born Cara Jocelyn Delevingne on the
12th of August 1992 on the mean streets of

34.text:
London. Me and my two older sisters, Chloe
and Poppy, are known as the Divine Delevigne’s.

38.text:
Were sort of like the English equivalent of
the Kennedy’s, except instead of actually

43.text:
getting shot, we just get shot dirty looks.
My mother Pandora is a London socialite and

47.text:
best friends with the Duchess of York, Sarah
Ferguson. Her mother was the lady in waiting

52.text:
to Princess Margaret. My father Charles Hamar
Delevingne is a property developer. My godfather

57.text:
is the president of the publishing company
of GQ, Vogue, Vanity Fair and Glamour magazine.

64.text:
My godmother is the acting icon Joan Collins.
But I hate it when people say that my rise

67.text:
to fame is the consequence of nepotism...
because they never tell me what nepotism means???

72.text:
Sure I come from money and yes my sisters
and I were expensively educated at a prestigious

77.text:
boarding school, but it hasn’t all been
easy. As a child I suffered from dyspraxia,

82.text:
a problem coordinating my thoughts and movements...
or what Naomi Campbell calls her modeling

87.text:
career. My mother also suffered from a long
term addiction to heroin, because it doesn’t

91.text:
qualify as a drug problem if you can afford
it. I first began modelling at the age of

95.text:
10, I appeared in Italian Vogue, photographed
by Bruce Weber. I also appeared in an advert

101.text:
for Cadbury’s chocolate, I had to walk down
a catwalk, Twirl, then Curley-Wurley.

107.text:
Music was my first passion though. I can sing,
and play the guitar, and play the drums. Before

112.text:
I became a model I recorded two albums with
Simon Fuller, the manager of the Spice Girls.

117.text:
I was even offered the chance to play Victoria
Beckham in the Spice Girls musical Viva Forever,

121.text:
but all they wanted me to do was point, pout
and looked like I just ate a lemon. So I said

126.text:
zig-a-zing nah! Instead I was spotted by Sarah
Doukas, the founder of Storm modelling agency,

133.text:
the same woman who found Kate Moss, and my
older sister slash model Poppy. She ‘discovered’

138.text:
me in 2009 after I had been best friends with
her daughter for most of my life.

143.text:
I made my first catwalk appearance at the
2011 London Fashion Week and my distinctive

149.text:
eyebrows, well... raised a few eyebrows of
their own. From there I went on to strike

153.text:
a pose for Yves Saint Laurent, Burberry and
Chanel. Earn my wings at the Victoria’s

158.text:
Secret Fashion Show. And Win Model Of The
Year at the British Fashion Show Awards in

162.text:
2012 and 2014. But modeling is a young woman’s
game, unless you're Naomi Campbell. Being in

169.text:
my early 20s I’m almost over the hill. That’s
why I decided to become her Royal Highness

174.text:
of Hollywood. I made my movie debut acting
alongside Keira Knightley in Tolstoy’s Anna

179.text:
Karenina in 2012. Critics said my non speaking
role as Princess Sorokina reminded them of

185.text:
the ‘outstanding features’ of Jack Nicholson,
Colin Farrell and Jake Gyllenhaal. Now you

191.text:
can see me in my breakthrough role in Paper
Towns, then acting opposite Johnny Depp in

195.text:
London Fields or as the villainess Enchantress
in Suicide Squad. I’m the omnipresent It

201.text:
I earn 10 thousand dollars a day and I’ve
got over 15 millions followers on Instagram.

206.text:
But money and fame can’t buy you friends,
so it’s a good thing that I’m so popular.

209.text:
Rihanna, Kendall, Harry Styles,
Taylor Swift, Justin Bieber everybody wants

214.text:
to be seen with Cazza D. But I soon learnt
that Hollywood is just like one big High School,

219.text:
and only one girl can be head cheerleader,
Taylor decides who the cool kids are, and

223.text:
she let me play Mother Chucker in her video
for Bad Blood which broke the vevo record

227.text:
for most views in 24 hours. I can still hold
a note myself though, as I showed when I dueted

233.text:
with Pharrell Williams. I even bagged a musician
of my own. I’m dating St. Vincent, but sorry

239.text:
boys don’t let her name mislead you. Just
like my eyebrows I’m out, loud and proud!

244.text:
That was my draw my life, don’t forget to
subscribe for more great videos. Later dudes!
